<MELItem itemNbr="32-45-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-32-45-03.1.2-32-45-03">
<Title>Nose Gear Spin Brake</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="0" opsIndicator="(O)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Use of flaps 20 for takeoff is prohibited.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Gear remains down for 2 minutes before retraction after takeoff.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
<Para>May be inoperative or missing provided:  </Para>
<Note>
<Para>In the event of engine failure after V1, retract landing gear after takeoff. </Para>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Increase flight planning fuel by 600 lb (272 kg). </Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Use of flaps 20 for takeoff is prohibited.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>After takeoff, leave the landing gear extended for a minimum of two minutes to allow the wheels to spin down prior to gear retraction.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>In case of engine failure after V1, landing gear should be retracted after takeoff.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>It is not necessary to apply landing gear extended takeoff performance adjustments when dispatching under this item.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
